2. The new function `close_orphaned_failure_runs` needs to handle a different case: runs that have a FailureObserved event but no RunCompleted for the same run_id. This is for runs that were killed externally (SIGKILL, GH Actions cancellation) where the panic hook never fired. Also, the existing `install_panic_hook` used to NOT emit RunCompleted before Day 142, so old runs may also be orphaned.

